history.content: I dropped the class and re-added myself to the end of the waitlist after following advice from an email that suggested switching to an open lab section, even if it would compromise my position on the lecture waitlist. Now I am 48 on the lecture waitlist and the lab I intend to enroll in is open. What are my chances of being able to enroll in the class? I really need to take the class this semester, and did not receive priority since I'm a Junior. Is there anything else I should do to improve my chances of enrolling in the class? Thanks in advance!
history.subject: EE16B Waitlist Chances/Logistics
